Chongqing: Jinfoshan Mt. ( N29.10° , E107.21° ). The labels of type series only indicate the locality Chung-King (= Chongqing). But the preface of the original literature (
Jedlicka 1931
) indicated that all material was collected from Kinfushan (= Jinfoshan) of Chung-king (= Chongqing) in May and June 1929.
